project.name: linear_regression
project.description:
This project demonstrates the use of online linear regression on streaming data. It has an insert only input stream consisting of: 1. An id that acts as the streams key 2. A y coordinate of data 3. 784 x coordinates
The project has a single continuous query with a source window that receives the data to be scored, a train window that generates and periodically updates the linear regression model, and a score window that performs online scoring.

window-source.name: w_data
window-source.description: Source window with file socket connector to publish provided example data.

window-train.name: w_train
window-train.description:
This training window looks at all the observations and periodically generates a new model using the linear regression algorithm. Model events are published to the score window w_scoring.
The following properties govern the linear regression algorithm in the train window for this example: nInit: specifies the number of data events used during initialization. commitInterval: specifies the number of data events to process before triggering a commitment of the model to downstream scoring. dampingFactor: specifies the damping factor alpha for old data points. centerFlag: specifies whether to center the data(dense part) based on the first batchSize data events of the initialization.Specifically, the mean is computed with the first bufferSize data events of the initialization, and each data event is subtracted with the computed mean. scaleFlag: specifies whether to scale the data (dense part) based on the first batchSize data events of the initialization. Data is scaled so that the variance of the first batchSize number of events is 1.
The input-map specifies the list of variable names to be used in classification. Variable names are defined in the input schema and they are separated by a comma in the list(for example, x,y). Additionally it specifies a target response variable, y.

window-score.name: w_score
window-score.description:
This scoring window scores the data from the source window, using the model produced by the training window. The following properties within the input-map and output-map govern the linear regression algorithm in the score window:
inputs: specifies the list of variable names to be used in classification. Variable names are defined in the input schema, and they are separated by commas in the list.
yPredictOut: specifies the predicted response. If not specified, it is not displayed. modelIdOut: specifies the column or field name in the output schema that stores the ID of the model from which the score is computed. If not specified, it is not displayed.
